Obesity:

• Fat is stored in the body as a reserve of energy
• Excessive fat in the body leads to obesity
• A useful measure of body weight is BMI or Body Mass Index
• When a person weighs 20% over the ideal body weight, he or she is obese

Causes:

• Excessive intake of high calorie food
• Genetic factors
• Metabolic disorder
• Certain medications

